{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Previews-Article"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI previews are a great way to work on your project in Xcode without having to launch an app all the time. Just update your views and models, and the preview will automtically update."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has preview-specific services and state, that can be used in your previews. This makes it easy to set up and preview your keyboard-specific views directly in Xcode."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/KeyboardKit\/KeyboardKitPro","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" unlocks powerful keyboard preview components. Information about Pro preview features can be found further down.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Preview-specific state & services","anchor":"Preview-specific-state--services","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit adds preview-specific shorthand for all services and states. For instance, "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardContext","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" has a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardContext\/preview","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance, the "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardInputViewController","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" has a "},{"type":"reference","identi